Would I fly to a hot-zone right now? Personally, probably not, if I could avoid it. But at the moment, given everything we know now, our overall risk, and the fact that I am lucky enough to be able to work from self-quarantine, I feel confident about continuing to travel.

Finally, there’s the fact that, even though we’re fortunate enough to travel (relatively) often, this is a true bucket list vacation that we’ve wanted to do for years. Given the extremely low overall risk, coupled with sunk costs, we’re going for it.
(There’s also an economic aspect. With the entire travel and travel-adjacent industry bracing for a disaster, it’s hard to feel guilty about engaging with it, to the extent that we can safely.)

However, my office has implemented an “encouraged” 0–day self-quarantine after air travel, and my wife’s has a similar policy in place. We plan to take advantage of this and practice social distancing until we know we’re in the clear, to avoid putting others at risk.
